comment:
Heres the truth...
WB is cleaning house due to AT&T.
Their plans are getting scrapped after Zack Snyder's Justice League was a decent-sized hit for HBO Max.
WB trying to sabotage the project by saying they are not going forward with the Snyderverse and attacking the fandom has pissed AT&T off.
The current DC multiverse (not DCEU since that's the snyderverse and everything else has been rebranded many times at this point) is on its last legs with the suicide squad and batman being the current projects they are looking at after the disasters of WW84 and Birds of Prey.
Mark my words... whether WB likes it or not, it's over for them.
AT&T has the cards and doesn't give two craps what WB thinks, they are the controlling party and aren't going to take the sabotages lightly with those future plans WB wants to do.
